    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offering a mechanically robust 2004 BMW M3 (E46) powered by the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six. This engine features individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system that has been recently overhauled to ensure optimal torque delivery across the rev range. The chassis benefits from proactive rear subframe reinforcement, addressing the platform's known structural fatigue points. Power is managed through a precise 6-speed Getrag manual gearbox and a variable M-differential lock for superior traction out of corners. The suspension geometry remains true, providing the communicative steering feel and balanced weight distribution this chassis is famous for. Maintenance is up to date, including a cooling system refresh and valve clearance adjustment, ensuring this M3 performs exactly as the engineers in Garching intended.",
